  "storyline": "# Storyline\n\n## Context\n\nAcute-stress episodes are hard to catch in the moment; wearable physiological signal offers a continuous, non-invasive monitoring lens if it can be modeled reliably across people.\n\n## Workflow\n\nMulti-channel sensor ingestion → per-channel feature engineering → dimensionality reduction → sequence modeling → subject-level validation → interpretable classification output.\n\n## Technical Implementation\n\n- **Ingestion:** Empatica E4 streams (BVP, HR, EDA, TEMP, ACC) across 15 participants, resampled to aligned frequencies.\n- **Features:** 30+ temporal/statistical features per channel, PCA (~40% reduction) and Z-score normalization for stable inputs.\n- **Modeling:** Bi-LSTM and CNN-LSTM classifiers (TensorFlow + Scikit-learn), 0.81 F1 (~79% accuracy).\n- **Validation:** Leave-One-Group-Out CV across 15 participants simulating unseen-user generalization.\n\n## Outcomes\n\nFramed sensor-driven classification as a daily-wearable monitoring concept, translating model outputs into interpretable classification outputs for downstream review."
